from __future__ import annotations

"""
Standalone FrameVision timeline editor prototype.

Milestone v20 focus:
- keep one shared time<->pixel conversion model
- stable ruler / zoom / scroll / playhead behavior
- media bin with ffprobe duration detection
- shared ffmpeg/ffprobe/ffplay resolver: /presets/bin, /bin, PATH
- dynamic track manager with rename/add/remove/reorder
- real file clips on the timeline, saved in project JSON
- collapsible Media / Timeline / Preview / Logs sections for more workspace
- compact preview pane with selected media/clip info
- clip trim handles with safe source-duration clamping
- selected media / selected clip playback through the FrameVision Qt preview player
- same-track timeline playback can cross gaps using a black preview + timeline clock
- top-track visual priority playback with visible/solo eligibility
- track control foundation: visible, mute, solo, lock
- active playback status label
- preview audio modes: Mix all audio / Video only / Audio tracks only / Mute
- v17/2 audio-track mode stability: silent visual player + cached audio source
- embedded ffplay remains only as an optional fallback, not the primary preview path
- target track selector and drag/drop from Media Bin to timeline

Run:
    python helpers/timeline_editor.py

Self-test only:
    python helpers/timeline_editor.py --self-test
"""

